2026-04-09 15:13:20 - Agent_20260409151101 - INFO - [+] Agent signaled completion: Reviewed 5 CodeQL queries all targeting command injection in `PerfectoBuildWrapper.java`. Confirmed 2 critical true positive OS command injection vulnerabilities in the `getTunnelId` method:

1. **Line 163-164 (Windows path)**: User-controlled fields `perfectoConnectLocation`, `perfectoConnectFile`, and `pcParameters` (set via `@DataBoundConstructor` with no sanitization) are concatenated into a command string passed as the third argument to `cmd.exe /c`, enabling shell metacharacter injection on Windows.

2. **Line 166-167 (Linux/Mac path)**: Same user-controlled fields are concatenated into a command string passed as the third argument to `bash -c`, enabling shell metacharacter injection on Linux/Mac. `perfectoConnectLocation` appears twice (in the `cd` portion and through `baseCommand`), providing multiple injection vectors.

Both findings are confirmed true positives with high confidence (98%). No sanitization, allowlisting, or escaping is applied to any of the user-controlled fields before they reach the shell execution call.
